description.narrative: Cross-cutting issues systematically addressed and monitored by the country office with strong focus on adolescents, gender, and youth issues and using innovation as a change strategy. 2,664,115 adolescent girls reached with services and skills. GenU country landscape assessment completed. 10 youth-led engagement and skilling centers established in community libraries. Local Conference of Youth on Climate produced national youth statement for COP26 advocacy. Youth Climate Council established. UNICEF StartUp Lab graduated a cohort of 22 companies. Three local solutions registered in the DPG database. 18,000 geolocations and 34,878 towns in Ghana included into the GIGA global platform. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2022
